        "description": "<div>\n<a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/upguard\">UpGuard</a>’s mission is to protect the world’s data. We obsessively seek out elegant, robust ways to enable our customers to find, acknowledge, and remediate cyber risks. With <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/upguard\">UpGuard</a>, organizations leverage our security expertise and software to automate what was once laborious, spreadsheet-driven processes–whether it's monitoring the attack surface of hundreds of vendors or assessing the security of their own infrastructure. <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/upguard\">UpGuard</a> is used by some of the world’s largest, fastest-growing, and most innovative companies.  </div><h3>About the role:</h3><div>We are seeking a VP, of Corporate Development, with a proven track record of successfully generating new business and influencing policy within the Government, Defense, and Technology sectors across multiple geographies. The successful candidate will have a strong understanding of the landscape in these sectors, particularly in the USA, Oceania, and Europe, and will help to establish and grow <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/upguard\">UpGuard</a>'s presence in these markets.</div><h3>What you'll accomplish</h3><ul>\n<li>Develop and implement strategic plans to generate new business within the Government, Defense, and Technology sectors across the USA, Oceania, and Europe.</li>\n<li>Lead complex deal negotiations involving multiple parties, often with differing agendas.</li>\n<li>Identify, evaluate, and prioritize potential business opportunities and strategic partnerships in line with <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/upguard\">UpGuard</a>'s vision and strategy.</li>\n<li>Build and maintain relationships with key Government, Defense, and Technology stakeholders.</li>\n<li>Collaborate with various teams within <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/upguard\">UpGuard</a> to ensure a comprehensive and coordinated approach to these sectors.</li>\n<li>Remain up-to-date on industry trends, regulatory changes, and potential opportunities in cybersecurity.</li>\n<li>Provide leadership and guidance to the Corporate Development team.</li>\n</ul><h3>What you'll need</h3><ul>\n<li>Minimum of a Bachelor’s degree in Business, Cybersecurity, Technology, or related fields. An MBA or related advanced degree is preferred.</li>\n<li>10+ years of experience in a strategic role within the Government, Defense, or Technology sectors.</li>\n<li>Proven track record of developing and implementing successful strategies in these sectors.</li>\n<li>Strong negotiation skills with the ability to close complex, high-value deals.</li>\n<li>Exceptional relationship-building skills with a wide range of stakeholders.</li>\n<li>Deep understanding of the cybersecurity landscape in the USA, Oceania, and Europe.</li>\n<li>Willingness to travel as needed.</li>\n</ul><h3>What we offer</h3><ul>\n<li>\n<b>Rapidly growing user base: </b>Work directly with some of the world’s largest, fastest-growing, and most innovative companies</li>\n<li>\n<b>Interesting problems at scale:</b> Deeply explore the ever-evolving world of cybersecurity with a platform processing billions of data points daily</li>\n<li>\n<b>Learn from industry-leading experts: </b>Our security research has been featured in <a href=\"https://www.nytimes.com/2018/07/20/business/suppliers-data-leak-automakers.html\" class=\"postings-link\">The New York Times</a>, <a href=\"https://www.newyorker.com/tech/annals-of-technology/the-wild-west-of-online-political-operatives\" class=\"postings-link\">The New Yorker</a>, <a href=\"https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2019/04/03/millions-sensitive-facebook-user-records-were-left-exposed-public-web-security-researchers-say/\" class=\"postings-link\">The Washington Post</a>, <a href=\"https://techcrunch.com/2018/07/20/data-breach-level-one-automakers/\" class=\"postings-link\">TechCrunch</a>, <a href=\"https://news.bloomberglaw.com/privacy-and-data-security/retail-customer-data-exposure-spotlights-cloud-security-risk\" class=\"postings-link\">Bloomberg</a>, <a href=\"https://www.gizmodo.com.au/2020/01/amazon-engineer-leaked-private-encryption-keys-outside-analysts-discovered-them-in-minutes/\" class=\"postings-link\">Gizmodo</a>, <a href=\"https://www.engadget.com/2020-02-21-tetrad-database-exposed-for-120-million-households.html\" class=\"postings-link\">Engadget</a>, <a href=\"https://www.forbes.com/sites/thomasbrewster/2019/01/16/massive-oklahoma-government-data-leak-exposes-7-years-of-fbi-investigations/#282ca1236e11\" class=\"postings-link\">Forbes</a>, <a href=\"https://www.zdnet.com/article/data-breach-exposes-cambridge-analyticas-data-mining-tools/\" class=\"postings-link\">ZDNet</a>, and <a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2019/apr/03/facebook-data-public-servers-amazon\" class=\"postings-link\">The Guardian</a>\n</li>\n<li>\n<b>Impact:</b> See the impact of your work on a daily basis, with data and impact available on dashboards you have access to</li>\n<li>\n<b>Generous compensation: </b>We're offering a base salary range for this role of between $230,000 - $250,000 + equity. Compensation offered will be determined by factors such as location, level, job-related knowledge, skills, and experience.</li>\n<li>\n<b>Competitive benefits: </b>We offer a range of benefits to support the holistic well-being of our team.  These include a generous PTO package and paid parental leave, flexible work arrangements, and professional growth and development opportunities - supported by an annual personal development budget. </li>\n<li>\n<b>Dynamic and supportive work environment: </b>We understand what matters to our people and give them what they need to do their best work.</li>\n</ul><div>If you believe you have what it takes to contribute significantly to our team, we'd love to hear from you. Please apply with your updated CV and a cover letter. </div><div>\n<a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/upguard\">UpGuard</a>'s mission is to protect businesses against the ever-growing cyber threats in today's digital world. Our success and growth lie in our team members' diversity, unique backgrounds, experiences, and ideas.<b> Join us and become part of this exciting journey!</b>\n</div><div>\n<a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/upguard\">UpGuard</a> is an equal opportunity employer. We're committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity, or veteran status.</div><div><i><b>Please note candidates must have the legal right to work in the USA, and while this is a remote-based position, at this time, we can only support hiring in the following US states: WA, OR, CA, NV, CO, MO, IL, TX, FL, LA, and MD. </b></i></div><p>Originally posted on <a href='https://himalayas.app'>Himalayas</a></p>",
