        "description": "<h3>Hi there!</h3><p>We’re <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/eezy\">Eezy</a>, we make vecteezy.com and other related applications serving millions of active users from 150+ countries in 7 languages every month. We are a successful remote-first family-first 15-year-old self-funded company and we are very nice people. We are looking to add a mid-level frontend, backend or full-stack engineer to our Content Manager team—Content Manager is the app people use to upload photos, vectors and other resources to vecteezy.com. Our tech stack is a TypeScript React app frontend that uses a Rails 7/Grape REST API backend with Postgres, Redis, Kinesis, ECS, BuildKite, Jest, Playwright, RSpec—React Native and Kafka ecosystem are on the horizon.</p><p>You don’t need to be in the US, but you do need to be in one of the four primary US time zones. You’ll generally work M-F 8a-5p in your local time zone with an hour for lunch. We don’t have time crunches or on-call rotations or unnecessary meetings. You’ll have a daily 15-minute standup at 10a Central, a weekly 1:1 with your manager, every two weeks you’ll have two sprint-related meetings, once a month there’s an all-hands meeting and once a year we all get together for a couple of days. There are optional demo day meetings and lunch-and-learn sessions. Rarely will you get pulled into other meetings. We have a non-dogmatic two-week sprint cycle and maintenance Fridays every two weeks. We provide time for professional development during the work week.</p><ul>\n<li>A successful candidate will likely have deep experience in either Rails or React as well as experience with and a strong preference for remote work. </li>\n<li>They’ll be kind, helpful, flexible, motivated, self-directed and eager to learn new things. </li>\n<li>Excellent written and spoken English are required. </li>\n<li>Comfort expressing thoughts and ideas in writing is important as most of our collaboration is textual.</li>\n</ul><p>Does this sound like you? We’d love for you to apply! Does it sound like somebody you’d like to be? You should apply, too! Degree, no degree, formal training, self-taught--we don’t care as long as you can do the work. You should be comfortable working with people from diverse backgrounds and different countries.</p><p>Thank you for reading this far and have an <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/eezy\">Eezy</a> day!</p><h3>Benefits</h3><ul>\n<li>Health Care Plan (Medical, Dental  Vision)</li>\n<li>Retirement Plan (401k, IRA)</li>\n<li>Paid Time Off (Vacation, Sick  Public Holidays)</li>\n<li>Family Leave (Maternity, Paternity)</li>\n<li>Short Term  Long Term Disability</li>\n<li>Work From Home</li>\n<li>Training  Development</li>\n<li>Life Insurance (Basic, Voluntary  ADD)</li>\n</ul><p>Originally posted on <a href='https://himalayas.app'>Himalayas</a></p>",
