        "description": "<div>\n<a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/openinvest\">OpenInvest</a>, a J.P. Morgan Chase company, is a values-based financial services leader with a mission to align capital with social and environmental values. Founded in 2015 by FinTech and ESG veterans, <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/openinvest\">OpenInvest</a>’s platform unlocks a personalized and engaging end-to-end client experience, including dynamic custom indexing, impact reporting, proxy voting, and more. </div><div>Formerly a Public Benefit Corporation and supported in our mission by some of the biggest names in Silicon Valley like YCombinator, Andreessen Horowitz, and QED, <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/openinvest\">OpenInvest</a> was acquired by JPMC in June of 2021.  JPMC services are used in half of all American households: join us to help design and offer sustainable finance solutions on the greatest scale, nationwide and across the world.</div><div>\n<b>Visas</b>: <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/openinvest\">OpenInvest</a> is unable to apply for new visas for candidates, but existing visas can be transferred</div><div>\n<b>Note to candidates</b>: You will be hired as an employee of J.P. Morgan Chase</div><div>\n<b>Location:</b> Anywhere in the US</div><div>We are looking for a seasoned frontend engineer to join our growing team! </div><h3>What You’ll Do:</h3><ul>\n<li>Build robust, high-performance, and scalable applications</li>\n<li>Work with the design and product teams to develop new features that are focused on user experience</li>\n<li>Actively participate in product decisions, build and design technical architectures and ensure that we set reasonable development timelines</li>\n<li>Build reusable components and libraries for future use</li>\n<li>Mentor and guide other engineers</li>\n<li>Look for opportunities to improve team efficiency and work with your team to implement improvements</li>\n<li>Participate in code reviews and contribute to the development of best practices across the team</li>\n<li>Lead the development of front-end projects and ensure they are delivered on time and to a high standard.</li>\n</ul><h3>Who You Are:</h3><ul>\n<li>8+ years of extensive frontend experience </li>\n<li>You have a deep understanding of frontend technologies such as JavaScript, React, Redux, and GraphQL</li>\n<li>You also have experience with performance optimization techniques, accessibility, and browser compatibility</li>\n<li>You can craft intuitive user experiences and reusable components using React, backed up by a solid understanding of JavaScript and TypeScript</li>\n<li>You can troubleshoot and debug issues and have the ability to find creative solutions to complex problems</li>\n<li>You have solid experience working with jest, react-testing-library, cypress, and other related testing tools and frameworks</li>\n<li>You can communicate effectively with other team members, including designers, product managers, and other developers</li>\n<li>You have experience leading projects and guiding other engineers on your team</li>\n<li>You are comfortable working with new technologies and have the willingness to learn</li>\n<li>You have a keen eye for design and can ensure that the application is user-friendly and accessible</li>\n<li>You write understandable, testable code with an eye toward maintainability and scalability.</li>\n</ul><h3>Ideal Candidate:</h3><ul>\n<li>A senior full-stack engineer with a primary focus on the front end, who possesses a combination of technical skills, experience, and soft skills to be successful in this role</li>\n<li>Experience building and maintaining design systems</li>\n<li>Full stack development experience with Python, FastAPI, pandas, MySQL, etc.</li>\n<li>Experience working with Kubernetes and Docker</li>\n</ul><h3>Company Culture</h3><div>\n<a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/openinvest\">OpenInvest</a>’s core values are:</div><div>\n<b>·</b> Pursuing a challenging mission</div><div>\n<b>·</b> Thriving on transparency</div><div>\n<b>·</b> Maintaining high standards of integrity</div><div>\n<b>·</b> Guaranteeing the right to be heard</div><div>\n<b>·</b> Prioritizing personal growth</div><div>\n<b>·</b> Prioritizing diversity and inclusion</div><div>We aim to build a culture just as open and accountable as our products. We hold ourselves and our colleagues to high standards in how we treat each other, our communities, and our clients. As part of our team, you are willing to work hard, handle various responsibilities as necessary, and be passionate about long-term, company-wide goals. <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/openinvest\">OpenInvest</a> is an Equal Opportunity Employer. We value a diversity of perspectives and backgrounds in our team and culture.</div><div>\n<a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/openinvest\">OpenInvest</a> is committed to supporting the needs of its candidates and employees. Please don’t hesitate to ask if there are any accommodations we can make for you either during the hiring process or upon joining the company.</div><h3>Additional Information</h3><div>\n<b>· </b> We also encourage you to apply for this opportunity on the JPMorgan Chase Careers <a href=\"https://jpmc.fa.oraclecloud.com/hcmUI/CandidateExperience/en/sites/CX_1001/requisitions?keyword=&lt;a%20href='https://himalayas.app/companies/openinvest'&gt;OpenInvest&lt;/a&gt;lastSelectedFacet=LOCATIONSselectedLocationsFacet=300000000289738selectedPostingDatesFacet=30\" class=\"postings-link\">page</a>. </div><p>Originally posted on <a href='https://himalayas.app'>Himalayas</a></p>",
