        "description": "<p><a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/truelogic\">Truelogic</a> is a leading provider of nearshore staff augmentation services, located in New York. Our team of 500 tech talents is driving digital disruption from Latin America to the top projects in U.S. companies. <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/truelogic\">Truelogic</a> has been helping companies of all sizes to achieve their digital transformation goals.</p><p>Would you like to make innovation happen? Have you ever dreamed of building Products that impact millions of users? Nice! Then we have a seat for you on our team!</p><h3><strong>What are you going to do?</strong></h3><p>You will have the opportunity to work in a forward-thinking and growth-oriented environment, at a Artificial Intelligence Industry is the first of its kind in Orange County to apply a broad, automated AI/ML platform to the challenge of starting and launching new company ventures. We believe predictive AI can unlock the key to solving countless global problems in a predictive and preventative way. Built by some of the brightest applied AI/ML minds, incubating the future with companies built from the ground up with predictive AI at its core, turning the incubator/foundry/accelerator model upside down.</p><p>Occupy a unique position in the market, working on a project called \"Makana\" which is a platform aimed at bringing AI to business. The platform helps business users load data sets (spreadsheets, databases) and automatically creates machine learning models to provide insights and predictions.</p><ul>\n<li>The developer needs to be skilled in React, as this is one of the core technologies mentioned. They will likely be responsible for developing user interfaces and components using React.</li>\n<li>The developer should have experience working with API calls. This suggests that they'll be involved in integrating the platform with external data sources or services.</li>\n<li>The developer should understand how to represent objects locally for the client. This likely involves working with databases and ensuring that data is efficiently managed and retrieved.</li>\n<li>The developer may be responsible for Go-based backend development, microservices, or other tasks related to this language.</li>\n<li>Be involved in integrating these models into the platform, allowing business users to analyze their data and make predictions.</li>\n<li>Will likely need to communicate effectively in this environment.</li>\n<li>Should understand business requirements, especially in terms of data analysis, predictions, and providing user-friendly tools for business people.</li>\n</ul><h3>What will help you succeed</h3><ul>\n<li>Years of professional programming experience in React</li>\n<li>Proficiency with GO.</li>\n<li>Experience working with API calls.</li>\n<li>Experience working with ORM ((Object-Relational Mapping)</li>\n</ul><p>Originally posted on <a href='https://himalayas.app'>Himalayas</a></p>",
