        "description": "<h3>About the Role:</h3><div>\n<a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/included-health\">Included Health</a>’s Care Team Experience team (CTX) is responsible for building, maintaining and improving the tools used by our care teams to help our care coordinators provide our members with world-class support and service. While much of our team’s work is internal-facing, we have a number of critical initiatives that require new or updated functionality in our member-facing mobile applications. </div><div>We’re looking for a Senior Mobile Engineer to take the lead in making these improvements happen quickly, effectively, and sustainably. You will play the lead role in the implementation and design of our team’s front-end needs within our existing mobile applications. You will closely partner with our Product and Design teams and other mobile engineers across the organization to ensure that the Care Team Experience’s mobile needs integrate seamlessly with the rest of <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/included-health\">Included Health</a>’s mobile experience.</div><div>This role will be responsible for working on both iOS and Android apps. While we will happily consider applicants who currently have expertise in only iOS or Android, the successful candidate will actively own CTX’s mobile experience in both iOS and Android. We’ll help you grow into the role, but you’re bringing the drive to do so.</div><h3>Responsibilities: </h3><ul>\n<li>Lead the Care Team Experience’s mobile development and vision</li>\n<li>Build, test, and deploy user experiences in our iOS application</li>\n<li>Measure and optimize the performance of the iOS application at scale</li>\n<li>Collaborate with Product Managers and Designers on planning and implementing frictionless user experiences</li>\n<li>Work with the team to continue development of best practices</li>\n<li>Be self motivated with the ability to make smart decisions and ask questions when necessary</li>\n</ul><h3>Qualifications:</h3><ul>\n<li>Bachelors or Masters in CS or similar field, or comparative practical experience</li>\n<li>5+ years of professional mobile development</li>\n<li>Experience building complex native mobile applications</li>\n<li>Command of either Swift and Objective-C or Kotlin, with a strong drive to grok all three</li>\n<li>Exceptional technical communication skills</li>\n<li>Experience integrating and leveraging external services for purposes such as user analytics, feature flagging, and authentication</li>\n<li>Solid understanding of mobile UI/UX best practices and standards</li>\n<li>Thorough understanding of RESTful API and application design</li>\n<li>Experience in our other technologies a bonus: GraphQL, JavaScript, React, ReactNative, AWS</li>\n<li>Continuous improvement: you’re not happy sitting on your laurels, and you thrive in an environment where an exceptional performance this year becomes the baseline expectation for next year</li>\n<li>Transformational leadership: you are constantly seeking out and identifying new and novel opportunities to improve our apps, and you take the lead in turning these opportunities into realities</li>\n</ul><h3>About <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/included-health\">Included Health</a>\n</h3><div>\n<a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/included-health\">Included Health</a> is a new kind of healthcare company, delivering integrated virtual care and navigation. We’re on a mission to raise the standard of healthcare for everyone. We break down barriers to provide high-quality care for every person in every community — no matter where they are in their health journey or what type of care they need, from acute to chronic, behavioral to physical. We offer our members care guidance, advocacy, and access to personalized virtual and in-person care for everyday and urgent care, primary care, behavioral health, and specialty care. It’s all included. Learn more at<a href=\"http://includedhealth.com\" class=\"postings-link\"><b>includedhealth.com</b></a><b>. </b>\n</div><div>-----</div><div><i><a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/included-health\">Included Health</a> is an Equal Opportunity Employer and considers applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, sex, orientation, national origin, age, disability, genetics or any other basis forbidden under federal, state, or local law. <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/included-health\">Included Health</a> considers all qualified applicants in accordance with the San Francisco Fair Chance Ordinance.</i></div><p>Originally posted on <a href='https://himalayas.app'>Himalayas</a></p>",
