        "description": "<p><em>We’re open to candidates located +/- 3 hours PT</em></p><p>The Resourcing Manager role at <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/metalab\">MetaLab</a> works closely with Sales, Client Services, and Project Management leadership and stakeholders to utilize the best mix of talent so our teams can deliver exceptional projects while enjoying their work. We’re a growing company, and you’ll be responsible for helping manage how we evolve our resource management and capacity planning.</p><p>You will use tools and an analytical eye to track and measure the efficiency of resourcing usage, and, based on this data, identify opportunities for improvements in our estimation and staffing in collaboration with other departments. The Resourcing team also works directly with our Talent Acquisition team and department leaders to facilitate appropriate hiring forecasting across the company. Above all else, this role’s success relies on staying one step ahead of things to ensure balance between new projects and team health. </p><h3>Responsibilities</h3><ul>\n<li>Working with teams to identify resource needs and allocate teammates based on each project’s requirements</li>\n<li>Working with Sales, Client Services, and Project Management leadership and stakeholders to understand new project pipeline and opportunities to build, maintain, and communicate resource forecasts</li>\n<li>Ensuring our team has the capacity to support opportunities and projects, identifying resource needs and excess</li>\n<li>Assisting Project Managers with resource allocation accuracy and challenges</li>\n<li>Managing vendor database, relationships, negotiations, and usage as needed</li>\n<li>Collaborating with our Business Operations team to establish tools, reporting, and process around all functions of resource management</li>\n<li>Performing capacity and utilization reporting and analysis</li>\n<li>Collaborate with Operations and Departmental leadership to define hiring forecasting and needs</li>\n</ul><h4><strong>The must-have shortlist</strong></h4><ul>\n<li>Change-oriented – You maintain a positive outlook in difficult situations. You work effectively in the face of ambiguity and shifting priorities, and are excited about contributing ideas for change and improvement.</li>\n<li>Problem Solving – You’re a strategic thinker who is able to use diplomacy, experience, and instinct to develop simple solutions to complex issues or competing demands</li>\n<li>Empathetic – it’s very little effort for you to demonstrate empathy, optimism, and patience in working with department heads and sales teams to work in service of each’s needs.</li>\n<li>Communications – You’re able to articulate ideas clearly and succinctly in a variety of settings and styles.</li>\n<li>Teamwork – You act as a catalyst for formulating a team-oriented environment to achieve common goals.</li>\n<li>Proactive – You don’t wait for others to surface challenges or issues you’re already seeing. You know that bringing forward issues is a strength and is crucial to this role’s success.</li>\n<li>Accountability – You assume ownership for achieving personal and team goals and don’t avoid flagging where support or clarity is needed.</li>\n</ul><h4><strong>Skills  Experience</strong></h4><ul>\n<li>3-5 years resource management experience in a product design agency</li>\n<li>Experience with vendor management, contracts, and negotiation</li>\n<li>Experience with Google Sheets/Excel and an affinity for data analysis</li>\n<li>Experience with Smartsheet and 10k Feet resource management software is a plus</li>\n<li>Assertive but empathetic conflict-resolution and problem-solving skills</li>\n<li>Highly detail-oriented and able to work autonomously</li>\n<li>Ability to prioritize and organize workload across multiple groups</li>\n<li>Strong ability to build relationships and trust with team members</li>\n<li>Strong willingness to learn and adapt in a fast-paced dynamic environment</li>\n</ul><div class=\"content-conclusion\">\n<h3><strong>Equal opportunity employer</strong></h3>\n<p><em>Research shows that women and other marginalized groups tend to only apply for a job when they meet every single criteria. Does this role sound like it was made for you, yet you don’t check every box? Reach out anyways!  We’re an equal opportunity employer and are dedicated to fostering an inclusive and diverse environment for employees from all walks of life.  We hire based on talent, and we’re proud of our global perspective.</em></p>\n</div><p>Originally posted on <a href='https://himalayas.app'>Himalayas</a></p>",
