        "description": "<div class=\"content-intro\">\n<h3>Join a leading fintech company that’s democratizing finance for all.</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/robinhood\">Robinhood</a> was founded on a simple idea: that our financial markets should be accessible to all. With customers at the heart of our decisions, <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/robinhood\">Robinhood</a> is lowering barriers and providing greater access to financial information. Together, we are building products and services that help create a financial system everyone can participate in.</p>\n<h3>As we continue to build... </h3>\n<p>We’re seeking curious, growth minded thinkers to help shape our vision, structures and systems; playing a key-role as we launch into our ambitious future. If you’re invigorated by our mission, values, and drive to change the world — we’d love to have you apply.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/robinhood\">Robinhood</a> has a primary in-office working environment; please be sure you have reviewed the preferred working location(s) for this role before applying.</p>\n</div><h3><strong>About the team + role </strong></h3><p>As the Sr. Manager, Payroll, you will manage all aspects of payroll for over 2,400+ employees. You will have the chance to serve as a key contributor on a strong team and to drive improvement of both the operational and technical payroll processes. The successful candidate will be someone who has contributed directly to the success and growth of the Payroll function in previous work experience and can bring their expertise and knowledge to <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/robinhood\">Robinhood</a>. This position will report to the Director, Payroll and Stock Administration and work closely with our People team as well as the Accounting team.</p><h3><strong>What you’ll do</strong></h3><ul>\n<li>Oversee the payroll processing for multi-state domestic and international exempt and non-exempt employees, including bi-weekly payroll and monthly or ad-hoc employee settlements</li>\n<li>Responsible for leading, training, and mentoring the Payroll team of 3 Analysts</li>\n<li>Assist in the documentation and support of month-end journal entries and reconciliations for payroll related accounts and participate in our month end/ quarter close processes</li>\n<li>Partner with the People Team, Corporate Tax, Accounting, Finance, Benefits, Compensation, Corporate Engineering and others to develop payroll best practices, guidelines and procedures and ensure proper flow of employee data and reporting</li>\n<li>Research, resolve and respond to escalated payroll inquiries from employees and/or partners</li>\n<li>Own and drive-to-completion payroll-related audits</li>\n<li>Develop, implement and maintain key policies and procedures for global payroll, including documentation of internal control procedures, identification of inefficiencies/gaps and implementation of process improvements</li>\n<li>Ensure tax reporting compliance, SOX and business controls are met each pay period</li>\n<li>Collaborate with various organizations within the Company to support the payroll process and to drive efficiencies and accuracy</li>\n<li>Manage existing vendor relationships with all key payroll related vendors. Lead planning for contract renewals, including vendor evaluation  providing recommendations.</li>\n</ul><h3><strong>What you bring </strong></h3><ul>\n<li>A desire to build and manage a world class global payroll function</li>\n<li>12+ years of relevant work experience, preferably in the public space, with 3 years of people management experience</li>\n<li>Expert working knowledge of Workday HRIS and Workday Payroll</li>\n<li>A passion to collaborate cross-functionally and build relationships in a team environment</li>\n<li>Experience with automating and streamlining processes</li>\n<li>Basic understanding of accounting for payroll related activities</li>\n<li>Strong leadership skills to support the needs of the business and the payroll team</li>\n<li>Willingness to roll-up your sleeves and jump in to make sure all deadlines are met</li>\n<li>Excellent verbal and written communication skills</li>\n<li>Excellent organizational skills and able to prioritize tasks and shift gears on a short notice</li>\n<li>Strong interpersonal and customer service skills and are a master at establishing and maintaining cooperative working relationships, with the ability to deal tactfully and courteously when explaining the functions and policies in the Payroll department</li>\n<li>Integrity and maintain the confidential nature of the information by protecting the privacy of our employees and their records</li>\n<li>Strong analytical and problem solving skills and are detailed oriented</li>\n<li>Knowledge in labor and payroll tax laws and regulations</li>\n<li>Fluency in MSOffice (Outlook, Word, Excel, PowerPoint), GSuite (Google Docs, Gmail), Slack or an equivalent, and comfort with MacOS</li>\n<li>Knowledge and experience with stock options and restricted share units (RSUs), including taxation of mobile employees,`</li>\n<li>Experience in a fast-paced international company</li>\n<li>You are bright, engaging, goal-oriented: a true team player</li>\n</ul><h3><strong>What we offer</strong></h3><ul>\n<li>Market competitive and pay equity-focused compensation structure</li>\n<li>100% paid health insurance for employees with 90% coverage for dependents</li>\n<li>Annual lifestyle wallet for personal wellness, learning and development, and more!</li>\n<li>Lifetime maximum benefit for family forming and fertility benefits</li>\n<li>Dedicated mental health support for employees and eligible dependents</li>\n<li>Generous time away including company holidays, paid time off, sick time, parental leave, and more!</li>\n<li>Lively office environment with catered meals, fully stocked kitchens, and geo-specific commuter benefits</li>\n</ul><div class=\"content-conclusion\">\n<p>Base pay for the successful applicant will depend on a variety of job-related factors, which may include education, training, experience, location, business needs, or market demands. You can view comp zones for our US office locations in the table below. For other locations not listed, compensation can be discussed with your recruiter during the interview process.</p>\n<p><strong>Office locations (by comp zone)</strong><br>US Zone 1: Menlo Park, NYC, Seattle, Washington DC<br>US Zone 2: Denver, Westlake (Dallas), Chicago</p>\n<h3>US Zone 3: Lake Mary</h3>\n<p>Click<a href=\"http://careers.robinhood.com/benefits\"> here</a> to learn more about <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/robinhood\">Robinhood</a>’s Benefits.</p>\n<hr>\n<p><a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/robinhood\">Robinhood</a> promotes diversity and provides equal opportunity for all applicants and employees. We are dedicated to building a company that represents a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, and skills. We believe that the more inclusive we are, the better our work (and work environment) will be for everyone. Additionally, <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/robinhood\">Robinhood</a> provides reasonable accommodations for candidates on request and respects applicants' privacy rights. To review <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/robinhood\">Robinhood</a>'s Privacy Policy please visit<a href=\"http://careers.robinhood.com/usapplicantprivacypolicy\"></a><a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/robinhood\">Robinhood</a> - US Applicant Privacy Policy. If you are an applicant located in the UK or EEA, please visit the <a href=\"http://careers.robinhood.com/GDPR\"></a><a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/robinhood\">Robinhood</a> - UK/EEA Applicant Privacy Policy.</p>\n</div><p>Originally posted on <a href='https://himalayas.app'>Himalayas</a></p>",
