        "description": "<div class=\"content-intro\">\n<p><a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/podium\">Podium</a> exists to help local businesses win. Using <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/podium\">Podium</a>, local businesses can simplify the way they communicate with their customers—from collecting payments to facilitating online reviews to launching marketing campaigns, and much more.</p>\n<p>Our work and focus on helping local businesses thrive has been recognized across the industry, including Forbes’ Next Billion Dollar Startups, Forbes’ Cloud 100, the Inc. 5000, and Fast Company’s World’s Most Innovative Companies.</p>\n<p>We look for people who are curious, creative and are willing to do the work to be a little better every day. We also embody our company values in all that we do, which always starts with being Customer Obsessed, followed by Be a Founder, Zero Drama, and Enjoy the Ride. Does that sound like you?</p>\n</div><p>We are looking for a VP, Design who will be responsible for driving the vision, strategy, and execution of our design  creative initiatives at <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/podium\">Podium</a>. You will lead the design function at <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/podium\">Podium</a>, overseeing a team of talented designers and design leaders to deliver exceptional solutions for our customers. Reporting into the Chief Product Officer, you will partner closely with cross functional teams including engineering, product, marketing and sales to craft compelling design strategies, identify user pain points, and scale <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/podium\">Podium</a>’s design practice.</p><h3>What you will be doing:</h3><ul>\n<li>Lead the Product Design and Creative teams a <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/podium\">Podium</a>\n</li>\n<li>Shape and evangelize a compelling design / creative strategy and vision at <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/podium\">Podium</a>, from the look and feel of the brand to how it translates into user journeys in the product and across marketing touchpoints</li>\n<li>Partner with product and engineering, and other cross-functional partners to deliver exceptional user experiences that drive impact for <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/podium\">Podium</a> users.</li>\n<li>Lead the Creative team in developing cut through marketing that tells the <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/podium\">Podium</a> story in a way that deeply resonates with our prospects/customers  drives results. </li>\n<li>Partner closely with marketing to drive a high impact creative roadmap. Continuously refine strategy based on performance results, customer insights, and business needs. </li>\n<li>Drive company-wide design definition, specification, and collaboration with cross-functional partners.</li>\n<li>Lead, grow, and inspire a high-performing team of designers, design leaders and creative professionals who are focused on the end-to-end <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/podium\">Podium</a> experience across our different segments of users, towards cohesion and successful results</li>\n</ul><h3>What you should have:</h3><ul>\n<li>Significant experience (8+ years) leading and managing product design and creative teams, including design leaders</li>\n<li>Experience leading and collaborating with diverse, distributed teams in a dynamic, rapid growth environment.</li>\n<li>Excellent communication, problem-solving and brainstorming skills – with ability to navigate and thrive in ambiguity</li>\n<li>Passion for building scalable solutions and services, working with (and simplifying) sophisticated design systems that span multiple products.</li>\n<li>Strategic thinking with the ability to balance creativity with data-driven decision-making.</li>\n<li>Proven experience working on a cross-functional leadership team where you deeply collaborated with engineering, product, and data teams to plan and implement team roadmaps.</li>\n<li>Customer-first mindset</li>\n</ul><h3>Benefits</h3><ul>\n<li>Open and transparent culture - Checkout this<a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ba2P5P9IMl0\"> video</a> to see what it’s like to work at <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/podium\">Podium</a> </li>\n<li>Life insurance, long and short-term disability coverage</li>\n<li>Paid maternity and paternity leave</li>\n<li>Fertility Benefits</li>\n<li>Generous vacation time, plus three 4-day summer holiday weekends</li>\n<li>Excellent medical, dental, and vision benefits</li>\n<li>401k Plan</li>\n<li>Bi-annual swag drops with cool <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/podium\">Podium</a> gear and apparel </li>\n<li>A stellar HQ (Utah) gym with local professional coaches and classes offered</li>\n<li>Onsite HQ (Utah) child care center, subsidized for employees</li>\n<li>Additional benefits for fully remote employees</li>\n</ul><p><em><a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/podium\">Podium</a> is an equal opportunity employer. <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/podium\">Podium</a> provides equal employment opportunities (EEO) to all employees and applicants for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity or expression, age, disability, genetic information, marital status or veteran status.</em></p><p>Originally posted on <a href='https://himalayas.app'>Himalayas</a></p>",
