        "description": "<p><a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/truelogic\">Truelogic</a> is a leading provider of nearshore staff augmentation services, located in New York. Our team of 500 tech talents is driving digital disruption from Latin America to the top projects in U.S. companies. <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/truelogic\">Truelogic</a> has been helping companies of all sizes to achieve their digital transformation goals.</p><p>Would you like to make innovation happen? Have you ever dreamed of building Products that impact millions of users? Nice! Then we have a seat for you on our team!</p><h3><strong>What are you going to do?</strong></h3><p>You will have the opportunity to work in a forward-thinking and growth-oriented environment, at a advertising American services company. </p><p>Occupy a unique position in the market, by working closely with the team on mergers and acquisition activities. You will be part of the Collaboration and Communications team, supporting over 80 companies and 14,000 staff worldwide. This team is devoted to providing best in class tools and methodologies that enable more frictionless work on behalf of our clients and partners.</p><ul>\n<li>Work closely with the Migration Manager to understand the scope of the migration project at hand.</li>\n<li>Ability to help design and deliver detailed scope of work documents based on project requirements.</li>\n<li>Promote optimization of current state architecture with modern solutions and automations.</li>\n<li>Provide timely and accurate status updates, keep leadership informed of key issues that may impact project completion, scope, and /or budget and interface with all areas affected by the project including end users.</li>\n</ul><h3>What will help you succeed</h3><ul><li>3 to 5 years working with migrations of millions of files.</li></ul><p>Originally posted on <a href='https://himalayas.app'>Himalayas</a></p>",
