        "description": "<div>We are looking for a hardworking Cloud Network Infrastructure Engineer to join <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/spotify\">Spotify</a>’s Core Infrastructure group! Our mission is to provide a coherent service platform for our customers to iterate faster, safely, and at scale.</div><div>Core Infrastructure’s goal is to provide world-class cloud-native infrastructure to <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/spotify\">Spotify</a>’s engineers. This involves key elements of our platform, including systems for observability, reliability, container orchestration and deployment, storage infra and auto-scaling tools, cost insights, service discovery, production networking, and perimeter ingress and egress. </div><div>We’ve been working on making our network more reliable, more self service for backend engineers, cost effective and multi-cloud.</div><div>Our team is responsible for all facets of networking across our cloud infrastructure.</div><h3>What You'll Do </h3><ul>\n<li>Collaborate with partner teams in AWS and GCP Networking on our Multi-Cloud Transit Network, playing a crucial role in designing and developing automation and large-scale services to guide our network towards increased autonomy. This will include responsibility for components from design through to deployment and operations.</li>\n<li>Design, document, and help to implement the next iteration of our network, incorporating advanced features like IPv6 and Direct Connectivity.</li>\n<li>Contribute to the redesign of our Virtual Private Clouds (VPCs) to include more regional failure domains instead of global, enhancing the resilience and reliability of our network infrastructure.</li>\n<li>Write and review code to automate problems within our squad’s domain, and ensure all systems are meticulously documented.</li>\n<li>Conduct periodic disaster recovery exercises, simulating events like regional network outages, to ensure system readiness and resilience.</li>\n<li>Take on complex system challenges, applying a measured and methodical approach to problem solving.</li>\n<li>Accept operational responsibility for the services owned by our team, including participating in an on-call rotation.</li>\n<li>Work as part of a geo-distributed team, with the majority of colleagues located in New York.</li>\n</ul><h3>Who You Are </h3><ul>\n<li>Robust experience in the design, administration, operation, and troubleshooting of highly scalable and resilient cloud network architectures on AWS, GCP, or Azure.</li>\n<li>Instrumental in implementing advanced network features like IPv6, Direct Connectivity, and SDN technologies.</li>\n<li>Actively participated in re-architecting Virtual Private Clouds (VPCs) to shift from global to more regional failure domains, enhancing network resilience and performance.</li>\n<li>Understands the challenges and solutions in crafting geo-distributed, fault-tolerant systems.</li>\n<li>Possesses extensive knowledge of network protocols such as BGP, IPSec, and OSPF, using them within various cloud technologies like CloudWAN, SharedVPC, and Transit Gateways.</li>\n<li>Deep understanding of Infrastructure as Code (IaC) and cloud orchestration tools such as Terraform, Ansible, and CloudFormation.</li>\n<li>Extensive usage of AWS and GCP services, such as IAM, VPCs, EC2, Kubernetes, and comfortable navigating the complexities of cloud security and compliance.</li>\n<li>A champion of standardization and automation, always seeking ways to streamline systems, improve the developer experience, and enhance system reliability and performance through relentless automation of operational tasks.</li>\n</ul><h3>Where You'll Be </h3><ul>\n<li>We are a distributed workforce enabling our band members to find a work mode that is best for them!</li>\n<li>Where in the world? For this role, it can be within the <a href=\"https://spotifyjobs.com/work-by-region\" class=\"postings-link\">Americas</a> region in which we have a work location and is within working hours.</li>\n<li>Working hours? We operate within the Eastern Standard Time zone for collaboration and ask that all team members be located in that time zone.</li>\n<li>Prefer an office to work from home instead? Not a problem! We have plenty of options for your working preferences. Find more information about our Work From Anywhere options <a href=\"https://spotifyjobs.com/work-from-anywhere\" class=\"postings-link\">here</a>.</li>\n</ul><div>The United States base range for this position is $156,275 - $223,250, plus equity. The benefits available for this position include health insurance, six month paid parental leave, 401(k) retirement plan, monthly meal allowance, 23 paid days off, 13 paid flexible holidays. This range encompasses multiple levels. Leveling is determined during the interview process. Placement in a level depends on relevant work history and interview performance. These ranges may be modified in the future.</div><div>\n<a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/spotify\">Spotify</a> is an equal opportunity employer. You are welcome at <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/spotify\">Spotify</a> for who you are, no matter where you come from, what you look like, or what’s playing in your headphones. Our platform is for everyone, and so is our workplace. The more voices we have represented and amplified in our business, the more we will all thrive, contribute, and be forward-thinking! So bring us your personal experience, your perspectives, and your background. It’s in our differences that we will find the power to keep revolutionizing the way the world listens.</div><div>\n<a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/spotify\">Spotify</a> transformed music listening forever when we launched in 2008. Our mission is to unlock the potential of human creativity by giving a million creative artists the opportunity to live off their art and billions of fans the chance to enjoy and be passionate about these creators. Everything we do is driven by our love for music and podcasting. Today, we are the world’s most popular audio streaming subscription service.</div><p>Originally posted on <a href='https://himalayas.app'>Himalayas</a></p>",
