        "description": "<div>At Weights  Biases, our mission is to build the best developer tools for machine learning. Weights  Biases is a series C company with $200 million in funding and a rapidly growing user base. Our platform is an essential piece of the daily work for machine learning engineers, from academic research institutions like FAIR and UC Berkeley to massive enterprise teams including iRobot, OpenAI, Toyota Research Institute, Samsung, NVIDIA, Salesforce, Blue Cross Blue Shield, Lyft, and more.</div><div>We are seeking a dynamic and strategic leader to join our team as the Director of Data. Reporting to the COO, the Head of Data will be responsible for leading data-driven decision-making across the organization by providing teams with the data infrastructure, pipelines, tools, and insights they need to make informed decisions. You will work closely with cross-functional teams, including senior executives, growth/marketing, product, engineering, GTM, and finance, to proactively identify opportunities and improve outcomes by leveraging key market, business, and product facts.</div><h3>Responsibilities</h3><ul>\n<li>Lead the development and execution of the company's data strategy, ensuring that data is at the forefront of decision-making across the organization</li>\n<li>Proactively, and in partnership with the functional organizations, identify areas where data can be impactful to GTM, RD, and GA teams. Taking into account the company’s product, buyer journey  sales motion, market context, and specific needs for metrics and analysis, you will build efficient and scalable data pipelines and interactive insights and visualizations that enable data-driven decisions across Weights  Biases</li>\n<li>Manage, mentor, and develop a team of data scientists and data platform engineers</li>\n<li>Continuously assess the effectiveness of data-driven initiatives and adjust as necessary to ensure maximum impact</li>\n</ul><h3>Must Have</h3><ul>\n<li>A strong background in end-to-end data science and analytics (from data engineering through insight generation), with a focus on business outcomes and proactive, cross-functional collaboration</li>\n<li>Strong leadership and communication skills, including the ability to effectively communicate data insights to non-technical stakeholders</li>\n<li>Proven experience in driving data-driven decision-making across an organization</li>\n<li>Experience with a variety of data visualization tools and techniques. Our evolving data stack currently includes Google BigQuery, Segment, dbt, Dagster, Stitch, Monte Carlo, Census, Tableau, and Mixpanel</li>\n<li>Strong problem-solving and critical-thinking skills</li>\n</ul><h3>Must Be</h3><ul>\n<li>Impact-driven: motivated by the opportunity to improve our business, product, and market position through data-driven exploration (more so than using a specific technology or tooling)</li>\n<li>Proactive: driven to be the “advance scout” - understanding our product  market context and identifying areas where data can be impactful to optimize our activities</li>\n</ul><h3>Our Benefits</h3><ul>\n<li>🏝️ Flexible time off </li>\n<li>🩺 Medical, Dental, and Vision for employees and Family Coverage</li>\n<li>🏠 Remote first culture with in-office flexibility in San Francisco</li>\n<li>💵 Home office budget with a new high-powered laptop</li>\n<li>🥇 Truly competitive salary and equity</li>\n<li>🚼 12 weeks of Parental leave (U.S. specific)</li>\n<li>📈 401(k) (U.S. specific)</li>\n<li>Supplemental benefits may be available depending on your location </li>\n<li>Explore benefits by <a href=\"https://remote.com/country-explorer\" class=\"postings-link\">country</a>\n</li>\n</ul><div>We encourage you to apply even if your experience doesn't perfectly align with the job description as we seek out diverse and creative perspectives. Team members who love to learn and collaborate in an inclusive environment will flourish with us. We are an equal opportunity employer and do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status. If you need additional accommodations to feel comfortable during your interview process, reach out at careers@wandb.com.</div><p>Originally posted on <a href='https://himalayas.app'>Himalayas</a></p>",
