        "description": "<p><a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/truelogic\">Truelogic</a> is a leading provider of nearshore staff augmentation services, located in New York. Our team of 500 tech talents is driving digital disruption from Latin America to the top projects in U.S. companies. <a href=\"https://himalayas.app/companies/truelogic\">Truelogic</a> has been helping companies of all sizes to achieve their digital transformation goals.</p><p>Would you like to make innovation happen? Have you ever dreamed of building Products that impact millions of users? Nice! Then we have a seat for you on our team!</p><h3><strong>What are you going to do?</strong></h3><p>You will have the opportunity to work in a forward-thinking and growth-oriented environment, at a company that  help drivers, riders, delivery partners, and eaters get moving in more than 10,000 cities around the world.</p><p>Occupy a unique position in the market, as an engineer to build systems for our very own employees. Our mission is to enhance corporate speed, reliability and worker happiness by building Products and Platforms. You will work closely with a highly capable team of engineers, data scientists, designers and product managers to ensure internal products and platforms are a powerful and innovative business advantage.</p><ul>\n<li>Demonstrate end to end ownership of critical new features and  infrastructure.</li>\n<li>Produce consistent high quality code across projects.</li>\n<li>Identify and fix bugs and reliability of current systems.</li>\n<li>Bring in your passionate self and positively impact the team around you.</li>\n<li>You'll work with your teammates in a disciplined agile development environment to solve diverse technical challenges.</li>\n<li>You'll build products and services that are highly available and scalable to serve our employees and global business groups.</li>\n<li>Dive deep into multiple tech stacks across the company.</li>\n</ul><h3><strong>What will help you succeed </strong></h3><ul>\n<li>Experience in backend development experience with Golang.</li>\n<li>Experience implementing sophisticated projects with multiple dependencies.</li>\n<li>Understanding and willingness to do activities that compliment Development.</li>\n<li>Experience working with Quality Automation of your own tasks.</li>\n<li>Understanding of Infrastructure and Deployment tasks to get application working in production.</li>\n</ul><p>Originally posted on <a href='https://himalayas.app'>Himalayas</a></p>",
